- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new notion of coherence for graphs and discusses its application in defining dynamic semantics for Multiplicative Linear Logic (MLL) extended with non-determinism. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of coherence relation in defining dynamic semantics for MLL, which is a formal language used in programming language theory. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another likely category as the paper discusses the finiteness and sparsity properties of the model, which are important considerations in data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the paper discusses non-determinism, which is a concept used in some machine learning algorithms. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper discusses the use of non-determinism in the context of MLL, which is a formal language used in some AI applications.
